# Chttrix — Phase 2 Principal Architect Audit
**Date:** 2026-03-04 | **Auditor:** Antigravity (Principal Architect Role)
**Scope:** Full-stack audit of `/client/src` + `/server/src` + `/server/models`

---

## Part 1 — Structural Map of the System

### Tech Stack Confirmed
| Layer | Technology | State |
|---|---|---|
| Frontend | React (Vite build), Tailwind CSS | Active |
| Backend | Node.js + Express | Active |
| Database | MongoDB via Mongoose | Active |
| Real-time | Socket.IO (in-memory; Redis adapter optional) | Active, Redis not yet wired |
| Auth | JWT (access 15m) + Refresh Token (HttpOnly cookie, hashed) | Solid |
| Encryption | E2EE layer — ECDH public keys on User, UMEK-based workspace key encryption | Partially active |
| Hosting | Vercel (client) + Google Cloud Run (server) | Active |
| AI | Chttrix Intelligence (`/api/ai`) | Route registered, maturity unknown |

---

### Architecture Map

```
Client (React/Vite — Vercel)
│
├── Auth Context → JWT access token in memory, refresh via HttpOnly cookie
├── Socket Context → socket.io-client → server WebSocket
├── WorkspaceContext / CompanyContext / DepartmentContext → REST APIs
│
├── Routing Layer (App.js — 620 lines)
│   ├── /workspace/:workspaceId/* → RequireAuth → RequireWorkspace → MainLayout
│   ├── /owner/* → RequireOwner → CompanyAdminLayout
│   ├── /admin/* → RequireAdmin → CompanyAdminLayout
│   ├── /manager/* → RequireDepartmentManager → ManagerLayout
│   └── /employee/dashboard → RequireAuth
│
Server (Node.js/Express — Cloud Run)
│
├── server.js (547 lines) — Single process entrypoint
│   ├── CORS, Helmet, CookieParser, Rate-limiter (auth only, 20 req/min prod)
│   ├── Input sanitization (sanitizeInput middleware)
│   ├── Socket.IO server + Redis adapter (optional, env-gated)
│   ├── Graceful shutdown (SIGTERM / SIGINT, 30s drain timeout)
│   └── Unhandled rejection guard (exits in production)
│
├── Middleware Layer
│   ├── auth.js — JWT verify → auto-refresh via cookie → attach req.user
│   ├── permissionMiddleware.js — Role-based guard
│   ├── permissions.js — Permission definitions
│   └── validate.js — Input sanitization (MongoDB injection prevention)
│
├── Feature Modules (/src/features — 31 modules)
│   Routes: auth, admin, channels, chat, company, employees, notes, tasks,
│           updates, workspaces, users, search, dashboard, ai, analytics,
│           audit, security, status, favorites, crypto, devices, etc.
│
├── Core Modules (/src/modules — 5 modules)
│   ├── messages/ → v2 message engine (channels + DMs)
│   ├── threads/ → thread replies
│   ├── conversations/ → E2EE conversation keys
│   ├── encryption/ → key management
│   └── identity/ → public key registry
│
├── Socket Layer (/src/socket)
│   ├── index.js — registers all handlers per connection
│   ├── handlers/messages.socket.js — conversation join/leave, DM send, typing
│   ├── handlers/huddles.socket.js — huddle start/join/leave/end/audio
│   ├── handlers/presence.socket.js — online/offline
│   ├── handlers/admin.socket.js — admin events
│   ├── handlers/meetings.socket.js — meeting events
│   └── handlers/polls.socket.js — poll events
│
└── Data Models (/models — 27 models)
    Core: User, Workspace, Company, Channel, DMSession, Note, Task, Update
    Supporting: ConversationKey, UserIdentityKey, Invite, Favorite, Department,
                Analytics, AuditLog, Billing, Broadcast, HistoryLog,
                InternalMessage, SupportTicket, Task, TaskActivity, etc.
```

---

## Part 2 — Feature-by-Feature Audit

### 1. Channels

**Model:** `channel.model.js` — workspace-scoped, privacy flags, member array with `lastSeenMessageId`, `admins[]`, `pinnedMessages[]`, `tabs[]`

| Dimension | Assessment |
|---|---|
| Feature definition | ✅ Well-defined. Public/private/default channels, per-member read state |
| Expected behaviour | Message delivery to `channel:<id>` room, per-user unread counts, admin controls |
| Current architecture | `channel.controller.js` (49 KB — very large), `channel.routes.js`, socket join via `chat:join` (legacy) and `conversation:join` (new) |
| **Missing logic** | ❌ No server-side enforcement that socket `conversation:join` caller is a member of private channels. The `join-dm` handler validates DMSession membership but the equivalent for `conversation:join` on channels does NOT query the DB. A user who knows a private channel ID can join its socket room. |
| **Missing logic** | ❌ `isMember()` on Channel model returns `true` for public channels unconditionally — no workspace membership check at the socket layer |
| **Missing logic** | ❌ Unread count computation: `lastSeenMessageId` exists in model but no confirmed endpoint/emitter that updates it on "channel viewed" |
| **Security risk** | 🔴 Private channel socket room is accessible without membership verification |
| **Security risk** | 🟡 `channel.controller.js` is 49 KB — high surface area, likely has inconsistent auth checks within. Needs audit. |
| **Reliability risk** | 🟡 Dual join events (`chat:join` + `conversation:join`) can lead to duplicate room membership. Idempotency check exists in `conversation:join` but NOT in legacy `chat:join`. |
| **Edge cases** | Last admin leaving — `isOnlyAdmin()` exists but is it enforced on leave? Unknown. |
| **Scalability** | Index on `{ "members.user": 1 }` exists. Missing compound index on `{ workspace: 1, isArchived: 1 }` for channel listing queries. |

---

### 2. Threads

**Module:** `/src/modules/threads/` — 2 files

| Dimension | Assessment |
|---|---|
| Feature definition | Thread replies to a parent message |
| Current architecture | Routes registered at `/api/threads` |
| **Missing logic** | ❌ Socket room for threads is `thread:<conversationId>` but it's unclear what the conversationId maps to (message ID? channel ID?). No confirmed `conversation:join` with `type: 'thread'` from client side. |
| **Missing logic** | ❌ No thread read state / unread thread count mechanism visible in models |
| **Security risk** | 🔴 No visible membership check before joining a thread socket room — any authenticated user can JOIN any thread room if they know the ID |
| **Reliability risk** | 🟡 Thread reply count was recently optimized (N+1 fix) — check if the aggregation is still correct post-refactor |
| **Edge cases** | What happens when parent message is deleted? Thread orphan handling not observed. |

---

### 3. Direct Messages (DMs)

**Model:** `DMSession.js` — workspace-scoped, 2 participants, unique compound index `{ workspace, participants }`, `hiddenFor[]`, `lastSeen[]`

| Dimension | Assessment |
|---|---|
| Feature definition | ✅ Well-defined. Workspace-scoped 1:1 DMs with E2EE-ready structure |
| Expected behaviour | Open/resume DM session, real-time message delivery, unread count |
| Current architecture | `join-dm` validates DMSession membership ✅. `send-message` socket event calls `messagesController.sendDirectMessage` via mock req/res. |
| **Missing logic** | ❌ `conversation:join` with `type: 'dm'` does NOT do DB validation (no DMSession lookup). Only the legacy `join-dm` handler validates. If client uses `conversation:join` for DMs, the security check is bypassed. |
| **Missing logic** | ❌ `lastSeen[]` field exists in DMSession but no observed socket emission to update it when a user reads messages |
| **Missing logic** | ❌ Company HQ scope: for company users, DMs are workspace-scoped — but cross-workspace DMs between company employees are mentioned as a requirement and not yet implemented |
| **Security risk** | 🔴 Mock req/res pattern for socket → controller is fragile. If controller checks `req.headers` or other HTTP-only properties, it will silently fail or skip validation |
| **Reliability risk** | 🟡 `io` is referenced in `send-message` handler but passed via `mockReq.io` — this works only if the controller reads `req.io`, not `app.get('io')` |
| **Edge cases** | Blocked users: `blockedUsers[]` on User model exists, but no enforcement in DM creation observed at socket handler level |

---

### 4. Notes

**Model:** `Note.js` — workspace-scoped, privacy-first (`isPublic`, `sharedWith[]`), `versions[]` (max 50), rich media attachments, `canView()` / `canEdit()` helpers

| Dimension | Assessment |
|---|---|
| Feature definition | ✅ Solid model. Private/shared/public notes, version history, media |
| Expected behaviour | Create/view/edit/share notes; auto-save versions |
| Current architecture | Routes at `/api/notes` and `/api/v2/notes` (same controller, dual-registered) |
| **Missing logic** | ❌ Dual registration of same routes (`/api/notes` and `/api/v2/notes`) with the same handler will cause route conflicts or redundancy. Needs cleanup. |
| **Missing logic** | ❌ No real-time collaboration (socket events for simultaneous editing). Two users editing the same note will overwrite each other. |
| **Missing logic** | ❌ Version snapshot limit (50) — is there a pre-save hook enforcing this? Not observed in model. |
| **Security risk** | 🟡 `isPublic` notes are visible to "all workspace members" but the workspace membership check must be done by the caller — confirm all GET endpoints enforce this |
| **Edge cases** | Very large notes with base64-encoded media — 50MB payload limit is set in server.js, which is appropriate. |

---

### 5. Company HQ & Dashboards

**Models:** `Company.js`, `Workspace.js`, `User.js` (companyRole, companyId)

| Dimension | Assessment |
|---|---|
| Feature definition | Enterprise workspace with Owner/Admin/Manager hierarchy |
| Expected behaviour | Owner dashboard, admin dashboard, manager dashboard, employee dashboard, company-wide user directory, cross-workspace DMs |
| Current architecture | Role-based routing (RequireOwner, RequireAdmin, RequireDepartmentManager). Dashboard routes at `/owner/*`, `/admin/*`, `/manager/*`, `/employee/*` |
| **Missing logic** | ❌ Company-scope messaging (DMs to ANY employee) — architecture is workspace-scoped. Cross-workspace DMs between company employees require a `company`-scoped DMSession or a separate model. Not currently implemented. |
| **Missing logic** | ❌ Company-wide user directory endpoint (search all employees) — `/api/search` exists but unclear if it's scoped to company |
| **Missing logic** | ❌ Owner Dashboard — billing page exists (`OwnerBilling`) but `Billing.js` model is minimal (1140 bytes). No payment integration observed. |
| **Security risk** | 🔴 `/api/admin-dashboard`, `/api/owner-dashboard`, `/api/manager-dashboard` routes do NOT pass through `requireAuth` middleware in `server.js` (lines 239-243) — they are mounted WITHOUT auth middleware at the express router level. This is a critical vulnerability if the route handlers don't enforce auth internally. |
| **Security risk** | 🟡 `rolesPerCompany` field on User is `Mixed` type — untyped and could be exploited via injection if not sanitized |
| **Edge cases** | Company suspension (`suspendedAt` on Company) — is there a guard that blocks suspended company users from accessing any workspace/channel? |

