### 6. Tasks

**Model:** `Task.js` — workspace-scoped, multi-assignee, 7-status workflow, epic/subtask hierarchy, visibility (private/channel/workspace), AI source flag

| Dimension | Assessment |
|---|---|
| Feature definition | ✅ Very well-defined model. Comprehensive workflow system. |
| Expected behaviour | Create/assign/track tasks, subtask hierarchy, status transitions, real-time notifications |
| Current architecture | Routes at `/api/tasks` and `/api/v2/tasks` (same controller, dual-registered — same issue as Notes) |
| **Missing logic** | ❌ No real-time socket emission observed for task creation/update/assignment. Users won't see task updates without polling or page refresh. |
| **Missing logic** | ❌ `TaskActivity.js` model exists but no observed hook that auto-creates activity log entries on status change |
| **Missing logic** | ❌ No enforcement that `visibility = 'channel'` requires `channel` to be set (application-level only, no model pre-save validation) |
| **Security risk** | 🟡 `canView()` accepts `userChannels` list from caller — if caller builds this incorrectly, visibility leak possible |
| **Edge cases** | Task deletion — `deletedFor[]` array exists (per-user soft delete) but `deleted: true` is a universal hard delete. The two mechanisms conflict. |
| **Scalability** | Good index coverage. Missing index on `{ company: 1, assignedTo: 1 }` for company-wide task views |

