## Part 3 — Production Hardening Audit

### 🔴 Critical Issues

| # | Issue | Location | Risk Level |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | **Dashboard routes unauthenticated** | `server.js` lines 239-243: `/api/admin-dashboard`, `/api/owner-dashboard` mounted WITHOUT `requireAuth` | CRITICAL |
| 2 | **Private channel socket room unauthorized join** | `messages.socket.js` — `conversation:join` does no DB membership check for private channels | CRITICAL |
| 3 | **Huddle join unauthorized** | `huddles.socket.js` — `huddle:join` has zero authorization | CRITICAL |
| 4 | **Huddle no WebRTC** | Voice/video is signaling only — not functional | CRITICAL |
| 5 | **DM via `conversation:join` bypasses participant check** | The new unified join handler skips the DMSession validation that `join-dm` does | HIGH |

### 🟠 High Issues

| # | Issue | Location |
|---|---|---|
| 6 | `socket.user.username` is always `undefined` | Socket auth only attaches `{ id }` not `{ id, username }` — affects all socket event payloads that read `socket.user.username` |
| 7 | Mock req/res in socket handlers | If controller uses HTTP-specific properties (headers, params), validation is silently skipped |
| 8 | Dual route registration for Notes and Tasks | `/api/notes` and `/api/v2/notes` mounted to same handler — potential conflict, confusion |
| 9 | No task/note real-time socket events | State-changing operations don't push via socket |
| 10 | No Updates socket emission | New announcements are invisible until page reload |
| 11 | No blocked-user check in DM socket handler | Blocked users can still initiate DM socket connections |
| 12 | No AI rate limiting | Potential cost/abuse attack surface |

### 🟡 Medium Issues

| # | Issue | Location |
|---|---|---|
| 13 | `isOnline: true` set on socket `connection` but never set `false` on HTTP disconnect | In `server.js` line 367-378 — HTTP path sets online, but socket `disconnect` event in `presence.socket.js` should also set `isOnline: false` in DB |
| 14 | `readBy[]` flat array on Updates | Does not scale — needs pagination or separate collection |
| 15 | Rate limiter only on `/api/auth` | No rate limiting on message send, file upload, search, AI endpoints |
| 16 | Missing `{ workspace: 1, isArchived: 1 }` index on Channels | Expensive channel listing without it |
| 17 | `rolesPerCompany` typed as `Mixed` | No schema enforcement |
| 18 | Company HQ cross-workspace DMs | Architecture is workspace-scoped. Company-scope DMs are not possible with the current `DMSession` model |
| 19 | Task `deleted` vs `deletedFor[]` conflict | Two different deletion semantics, inconsistently applied |
| 20 | No `pinnedUntil` TTL enforcement for Updates | Pinned announcements stay forever even after expiry |

### Race Conditions & Ordering

| Issue | Details |
|---|---|
| **Message ordering** | No `seq` or monotonic sequence field on messages. Ordering is by `createdAt` timestamp — clock skew on Cloud Run can cause misordering |
| **Concurrent DM creation** | Unique index `{ workspace, participants }` on DMSession prevents duplicate sessions at DB level ✅, but race condition at socket layer could trigger duplicate `send-message` events before DB constraint kicks in |
| **Socket room join race** | Idempotency check in `conversation:join` (`socket.rooms.has(room)`) — this is in-memory and correct for single-instance, but with Redis adapter across instances the check is unreliable |

