## Part 5 — Production Standard Checklist

### Messaging Reliability (Slack-level)
- [ ] Message delivery via HTTP POST (persistence first) + socket broadcast (real-time) — ✅ Architecture supports this
- [ ] `clientTempId` optimistic UI reconciliation — ✅ Implemented in DM send
- [ ] Message ordering: add monotonic `seq` field per conversation or sort by `_id` (ObjectId is monotonically increasing by insert time — use this as sort key)
- [ ] Offline message queue: on reconnect, client fetches messages since `lastSeenMessageId`
- [ ] Socket reconnection: client-side `socket.io-client` auto-reconnect configured — **verify `reconnectionAttempts` and `reconnectionDelay`**

### Permission Correctness
- [ ] Private channel: DB membership check on every socket JOIN
- [ ] Thread: DB membership check (parent channel) on every socket JOIN
- [ ] DM: DB participant check on every socket JOIN (`conversation:join` type `dm`)
- [ ] Huddle: DB channel membership check on `huddle:join`
- [ ] Notes: workspace membership verified on all GET endpoints
- [ ] Updates: Owner/Admin role verified on POST
- [ ] Admin dashboards: `requireAuth` middleware confirmed on all admin routes

### Data Isolation
- [ ] All queries scoped by `workspaceId` (never query messages/channels globally)
- [ ] Company users cannot access other companies' data (companyId filter on all company routes)
- [ ] Personal workspace users isolated from company workspace data

### WebSocket Resilience
- [ ] Client reconnects after network drop (test on mobile network switch)
- [ ] Server-side: presence accurately reflects disconnect (`isOnline = false` on `disconnect` event)
- [ ] Redis adapter: configure and test before scaling beyond 1 Cloud Run instance

### Database Indexing
- [ ] `Channel`: add `{ workspace: 1, isArchived: 1 }`
- [ ] `Task`: add `{ company: 1, assignedTo: 1 }`
- [ ] `DMSession`: existing unique `{ workspace, participants }` ✅
- [ ] `User`: existing `{ email: 1 }` unique ✅
- [ ] `Update`: existing `{ company: 1, workspace: 1, createdAt: -1 }` ✅

### Security Hardening
- [ ] Rate limit: extend to `/api/v2/messages`, `/api/ai`, `/uploads`
- [ ] Socket auth: only attach `{ id }` without `username` — intentional, but socket payloads should populate username from User lookup, not socket context
- [ ] Input sanitization: `sanitizeInput` is global ✅ — verify it handles nested arrays
- [ ] Helmet: active ✅
- [ ] HTTPS redirect: active in production ✅
- [ ] E2EE keys: confirm all private keys are server-side decryptable only via UMEK (not stored plaintext)

